Precautions Before use: Always wash the area to be bleached with cold water and dry normally. Do not use face wash or cleansers. If irritation, itching or burning continues, apply ice after removing bleach cream. It is safe for skin with pimples. Never mix the cream and activator until you are ready to start its use. Always store in a cool and dry place. Precautions Before use: Use of soap is not advisable after bleaching for at least 2 hours. Avoid going out into the sun after bleaching or use in the evening. Bell or Ghanti is an essential part of Puja rituals. It is used while performing Aarti to lend a melodious tone to the chanting. It drowns Inauspicious noises and brings Spiritual vibrations to the prayer ceremony.
A well-designed Ghanti or bell produce long strains of the sound OM. The most widespread belief is that the puja bell is sounded to invite the deity to accept the worship and prayers. Another belief is that it is to drive away the evil and negative forces.
The sound made from a well-designed Ghanti or Bell is uninterrupted, reverberating (echo), deep and impressive. Symbolically, the body of the bell represents time - Ananta. The tongue of the bell symbolically represents Goddess Saraswati. The handle of the Ghanti is considered to be the vital principle (Praan Shakti) and symbolically represents Hanuman, Garuda, Nandi or Chakra.

Bell or Ghanti is an essential part of Puja rituals. It is used while performing Aarti to lend a melodious tone to the chanting. It drowns Inauspicious noises and brings spiritual vibrations to the prayer ceremony. A well-designed Ghanti or bell produce long strains of the sound OM. The most widespread belief is that the puja bell is sounded to invite the deity to accept the worship and prayers. Another belief is that it is to drive away evil and negative forces. The sound made from a well-designed Ghanti or Bell is uninterrupted, reverberating (echo), deep and impressive. Symbolically, the body of the bell represents time - Ananta. The tongue of the bell symbolically represents Goddess Saraswati. The handle of the Ghanti is considered to be the vital principle (Praan Shakti) and symbolically represents Hanuman, Garuda, Nandi or Chakra.

product: Herb Bleach For Sensitive Skin With Haldi, Chandan, Aloe Vera, Nimbu
description:
The first gentle bleach for sensitive skin. This Haldi, Chandan, Aloe vera & Nimbu combination makes your skin fairer & beautiful day by day. The ultimate herbal solution to the unwanted hair growth on your skin. If you are looking for lighter-looking, beautiful skin, you are in the right place. Infused with Nimbu, nature’s very own bleach agent, Olivia Herb Bleach fades unwanted hair on your face, body and arms with surprising ease. Let the magic of Haldi and Chandan make you fairer day by day! For best results use every 15 days. Important note:  Always wash the area to be bleached with cold water and dry normally. Do not use face wash or cleansers. Always mix Bleach Booster containing activated carbon into the mixture of Cream & Activator to enhance Bleaching effect. Do not bleach after a hot bath as pores are open or immediately after exposure to sunlight. Avoid application of bleach around the eyes(eyebrows, eyelids etc.) Avoid use on broken, irritated skin. Mild irritation is normal with bleaching. However, if it starts itching or burning, remove it immediately. Next day, add more cream and then apply. The proportion of cream and activator varies according to skin types. If irritation, itching or burning continues, apply ice after removing bleach cream. It is safe for skin with pimples. Never mix the cream and activator until you are ready to start its use. Before each use perform a patch test and follow enclosed directions. Though meant for sensitive skin, you are still advised to conduct a patch test in a small area of the arm. Depending on your skin type, the effect of OLIVIA HERB BLEACH lasts for 2-3 weeks. However, it can be used again only after 15 days. Do not bleach after a hot bath. 
Points to remember: Use of soap is not advisable after bleaching for at least 2 hours. Avoid going out into the sun after bleaching or use in the evening. Do not keep aside the mixed bleach for re-use. For external use only/ keep away from children. Always store in a cool and dry place.

description: Reward your skin with instant fairness with the Olivia Oxygen Bleach. Olivia Oxygen Bleach comes with a specially formulated Pre-Bleach. This cream is a concentrate which moisturizes skin, reduces sensitivity and increases glow. It acts as an Oxygen Booster. Precautions Before use: Always wash the area to be bleached with cold water and dry normally. Do not use face wash or cleansers. Always store in a cool and dry place. Precautions Before use: Use of soap is not advisable after bleaching for at least 2 hours. Avoid going out into the sun after bleaching or use in the evening. Do not keep aside the mixed bleach for re-use.

Organic Jaggery is produced from sugarcane cultivated in organic farms spread across India without application of chemical fertilizers or pesticides. Processing is done without using any toxic and harsh chemicals used to clarify cane sugar. It is derived from the process of evaporation of raw sugarcane juice without separating the molasses from the crystals. It is known as "panela" in South America & Mexico, "gur" in India. It is characterised by a soft texture. Colour of Organic Jaggery varies from yellow to dark brown. Unlike refined sugar coming from chemical processing, Jaggery retains trace minerals and vitamins and hence is a healthy and nutrient-rich sweetener. It is often used in place of sugar for sweetening the beverages in rural India. None of the traditional Indian sweets is baked without the addition of Jaggery.

Organic Jaggery Powder is produced from sugarcane cultivated in organic farms spread across India without application of chemical fertilizers or pesticides. Processing is done without using any toxic and harsh chemicals used to clarify cane sugar. It is derived from the process of evaporation of raw sugarcane juice without separating the molasses from the crystals. It is known as "panela" in South America & Mexico, "gur" in India. It is characterized by a soft texture. Colour of Organic Jaggery varies from yellow to dark brown. Unlike refined sugar coming from chemical processing, Jaggery retains trace minerals and vitamins and hence is a healthy and nutrient-rich sweetener. It is often used in place of sugar for sweetening the beverages in rural India. None of the traditional Indian sweets is baked without the addition of Jaggery.

Organic Jaggery is produced from sugarcane cultivated in organic farms spread across India without application of chemical fertilisers or pesticides. Processing is done without using any toxic and harsh chemicals used to clarify cane sugar. It is derived from the process of evaporation of raw sugarcane juice without separating the molasses from the crystals. It is known as "panela" in South America & Mexico, "gur" in India. It is characterized by a soft texture. Colour of Organic Jaggery varies from yellow to dark brown. Unlike refined sugar coming from chemical processing, Jaggery retains trace minerals and vitamins and hence is a healthy and nutrient-rich sweetener. It is often used in place of sugar for sweetening the beverages in rural India. None of the traditional Indian sweets is baked without the addition of Jaggery.

Saffron is a wonderful aid in clearing & brightening up the complexion. Post-bleach serum with sunscreen protects your skin against tanning and imparts radiance for that special occasion. Precautions Before use: Always wash the area to be bleached with cold water and dry normally. Do not use face wash or cleansers. Always mix Bleach Booster containing Swarna Bhasma into the mixture of Cream & Activator to enhance Bleaching effect. Do not bleach after a hot bath as pores are open or immediately after exposure to sunlight. Avoid application of bleach around the eyes(eyebrows, eyelids etc.) Avoid use on broken, irritated skin. Mild irritation is normal with bleaching. However, if it starts itching or burning, remove it immediately. Next day, add more cream and then apply. The proportion of cream and activator varies according to skin types. If irritation, itching or burning continues, apply ice after removing bleach cream. It is safe for skin with pimples. Never mix the cream and activator until you are ready to start its use. Before each use perform a patch test and follow enclosed directions. Though meant for sensitive skin, you are still advised to conduct a patch test in a small area of the arm. Depending on your skin type, the effect of OLIVIA GOLD BLEACH lasts for 2-3 weeks. However, use after 15-20 days is strongly recommended. For external use only/ keep away from children. Always store in a cool and dry place.
